    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.11-12_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">11</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Arlington, Minnesota
                        May 4, 1959
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Willard and I have just leanred that you are going to be back in Minnesota for the annual Mid West Silver Lake Writer's Conference. This is good news, my Friend, for I intend to see you again, and Willard wants very much to meet you. He has, in fact, become very interested in the Conference itself, to my delight. We hope to spend at least one or two days in attendance, more if possible.</p>
                
                <p>Since you last wrote me, my "article" has begun to take on the dimensions of a book. I have proceeded cautiously and with a great deal of thought. As a matter of fact, I have been spending some time recently acquiring more detailed medical information concerning various methods used in the treatment of mental illness. There has been much written on this subject, but as far as I know, no one has used my apprach. I have discussed this wi<del>h</del><add>t</add>h two doctors from a nearby State institution who read my material and offered any help they could give. As a matter of fact, one of the doctors surprised me by asking me to supply mime<del>i</del><add>o</add>graphed copies of the unfinished material just as it is for distribution among the patients. However, much as I want to be of help, I hesitate to make such a mov<del>r</del><add>e</add> without the protection of a copyright. Have you any suggestions as to how I might handle this?</p>
                
                <p>By the way could you let me know which days you plan to spend at the Conference? We certainly don't want to miss you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Jessie Erickson</signed>                
                    <signed>Jessie H. Erickson</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
